description: Rick and the others try to restore order in the aftermath of a terrible discovery. Hershel takes up an old habit and disappears, Rick and Glenn must follow him into town.
name: Nebraska

description: Trapped, Rick, Hershel and Glenn fight to survive against new foes, both dead and alive. Shane finds Lori in danger on the road and makes it his mission to bring her back to the farm.
name: Triggerfinger

description: Rick and Shane come into conflict over the fate of an outsider. Andrea helps Hershel's youngest daughter face a crucial decision.
name: 18 Miles Out

description: Rick sides with Shane on an important decision, causing Dale to worry that the group is losing its humanity. Carl's actions have unintended consequences on the group.
name: Judge, Jury, Executioner

description: The group learns that someone dangerous may be on the loose near the farm. As night falls, Rick, Shane, Daryl and Glenn comb the woods to handle the situation and keep the group safe.
name: Better Angels

description: Rick and Carl return from the woods to find the farm in jeopardy. The group is split up in the ensuing chaos. With things looking grim, Rick’s leadership is questioned.
name: Beside the Dying Fire
The Frog is a Deadly Weapon

deck:
The Slitheen have taken control of the British government and plane to destroy the world! 
(part 2 of 2, the first being Aliens in London)
description: The world is in a huge amount of trouble as the Slitheen ready their nuclear missiles from Downing Street to start World War Three and the Doctor may not be able to help, as he and his companions are captured.
name: World War Three

deck: A religious fanatic tries to instigate the end of the world.
name: Milennium

deck: The perpetrator of a murder appears to have superhuman speed.
name: Rush

deck: Mulder and Scully meet a man who is abnormally fortunate. But he is hiding a tragic secret.
name: The Goldberg Variation

deck: A killer from a previous case decides that he has unfinished business, and comes after Scully.
name: Orison

deck: The return of the Daleks!
description: A damaged Dalek goes on a killing spree in a under-ground museum owned by a nasty millionaire and the Doctor and Rose are caught in the cross-fire, but is this Dalek actually capable of mercy?
name: Dalek

deck: Mulder and Scully investigate the murder of a magician.
name: The Amazing Maleeni

deck: A strange snake handling cult appear to be behind an unusual murder.
name: Signs and Wonders

deck: While investigating a child abduction case, Mulder begins to see parallels between the current case and his sister's unsolved disappearance.
name: Sein und Zeit

deck: The Doctor and Rose go to a TV news station in the 20 000th century  along with a new companion Adam. But is Adam worthy of traveling with The Doctor?
description: The Doctor is joined by a new companion Adam, and fights against a sinister force in the 20 000th Century. But can the Doctor trust Adam? And how many more people will die before he can get to the bottom of this mystery?
name: The Long Game

deck: Mulder finally learns the truth behind his sister's disappearance.
name: Closure

deck: Rose learns the laws of time.
description:
When Rose interferes in her own timeline she causes a chain of events which lead to 'Reapers' being let out onto our world killing people left and right because of the temporal rift cause by her.

But How will she stop this, the Doctor and the TARDIS are taken from her?
name: Father's Day

deck: Mulder and Scully become part of a Cops-style reality show.
name: X-Cops

deck: The main character in a fully immersive video game seems to have come to life.
name: First Person Shooter

deck: A doctor fears that his family have been cursed.
name: Theef

description: With the world growing increasingly more dangerous and Lori’s pregnancy advancing, Rick discovers a potentially safe haven. But first he must secure the premises, pushing his group to its limit.
name: Seed

description: After a traumatic event, a life hangs in the balance. Complicating matters, the group must also deal with a potential threat to their new surroundings.
name: Sick

description: Andrea and Michonne find a new community of survivors; a decision must be made.
name: Walk With Me

deck: It's WW2 and a mysterious virus is going around turning people into gas mask zombies.
description: A mysterious virus spreads through London in World War Two transforming people into mindless gas mask zombies and Rose meets the charming and charismatic Captain Jack Harkness, but what does he have to do with this outbreak?
name: The Empty Child

deck: The Smoking Man offers a cure for Scully's cancer - at a price.
name: En Ami

description: The group is severed, placing lives in jeopardy; Merle has a request for the Governor.
name: Killer Within

deck: The conclusion to the story that started in "The Empty Child"
description: The Doctor races to find a cure for the virus and confront's Captain Jack about his part in the spread. But will he be able to fix this in time? And is there any hope for the infected?
name: The Doctor Dances

deck: Mulder and Scully attempt to capture a female serial killer.
name: Chimera

deck: The return of the Slitheen or at least one of them.
description: The Doctor, Rose and Captain Jack faces one of the Slitheen who intends to use the rift in time, located in Cardiff to complete what was started in Downing Street by their brother and sisters.
name: Boom Town

deck: A hospital mix-up reunites Scully with a very important figure from her past.
name: All Things

deck: Skinner asks Mulder and Scully to assist him in the investigation of an unscrupulous tobacco company.
name: Brand X

deck: An old friend of Skinner attempts to make a film based very loosely on the X Files.
name: Hollywood A.D.

deck:
The first part to the epic conclusion to the first series of doctor who.
Also The Doctor Vs a Dalek Army!
description: The secret of the Bad Wolf will be revealed and the doctor faces off against the massive forces of the Dalek, but Rose may not make it out alive...
name: Bad Wolf

deck: Despite their attempts to get away from each other, the lives of two identical women are inexplicably intertwined.
name: Fight Club

deck: Two brothers stumble upon a genie who will grant their wishes.
name: Je Souhaite

deck: Part 2 of 2 to the conclusion of series 1. The Doctor returns rose home for her safety and the Bad Wolf stands revealed!
description: The Doctor returns Rose home to her family, for her safety but she won't stand down. The Doctor faces death and his army moves forth. The Dalek armada kills his friends while planing their final move and the only thing that can stop them is the Bad Wolf... but who is the Bad Wolf?
name: Parting of the Ways

deck: Mulder and Scully begin an investigation which leads them back to the scene of their first ever case.
name: Requiem

deck: With Mulder missing, Scully is assigned a new partner.
name: Within

deck: Scully, Skinner and Agent Doggett do everything they can to protect Gibson Praise after his location is discovered.
name: Without

deck: Scully and Doggett investigate their first case.
name: Patience

deck: Scully puts herself in serious danger when she ditches Doggett and attempts to carry out an investigation alone.
name: Roadrunners

deck: Scully and Doggett are stumped when a missing child is returned years after his abduction, but does not appear to have aged a day.
name: Invocation

deck: A man finds himself on trial for his wife's murder, with no recollection of how or why.
name: Redrum

deck: Doggett and Skinner join forces to solve a case.
name: Via Negativa

deck: Scully and Doggett face an interesting challenge when the prime suspect in their latest case appears to have x-ray vision.
name: Surekill

deck: A man comes back from the dead with the ability to transform into metal.
name: Salvage

deck: An Indian man appears to have a gruesome ability.
name: Badlaa

deck: Scully and Doggett try to resolve the last case Mulder worked on before he went missing.
name: The Gift

deck: After a series of murders, Doggett heads to Boston in search of the truth.
name: Medusa

deck: An encounter with a fellow abductee leads Scully to believe that her unborn baby might not be human.
name: Per Manum

deck: When a number of missing abductees begin reappearing, it gives the team fresh hope of finding Mulder alive.
name: This is Not Happening

deck: Krycek approaches with information about the newly returned abductees.
name: Deadalive

deck: Mulder decides to get straight back to work after his disappearance, in an attempt to learn the truth before he is removed from the X Files permanently.
name: Three Words

deck: Scully and Doggett's latest case seems to have ties to the death of Doggett's son.
name: Empedocles

deck: When more information is revealed about the black oil, Mulder and Doggett are forced to team up,
name: Vienen

deck: Doggett is assigned a new partner, but while investigating a strange reptilian monster, things begin to go awry.
name: Alone

deck: As Scully's pregnancy nears its end, the people around her fight to protect her and her unborn child.
name: Essence

deck: Scully decides to run away and have her baby in secret.
name: Existence

description: After another loss, Rick struggles. Michonne remains suspicious of the Governor as he throws a party with a unique twist for the people of Woodbury.
name: Say the Word

description: As Andrea grows closer to the Governor, Michonne makes a decision about Woodbury. Glenn and Maggie go on a run. Rick struggles.
name: Hounded

description: The Governor presses for information. A new guest arrives at the prison, forcing Rick's hand.
name: When the Dead Come Knocking

description: Andrea steps up as the people of Woodbury are thrown into uncharted territory. At the prison, a new threat arises.
name: Made to Suffer

description: Rick tries to rescue a member of his group. Woodbury is in disarray after a recent attack. New guests raise concerns at the prison.
name: The Suicide King

description: As the group debates their next course of action, Rick wanders after a lost friend. Daryl and Merle question their choices. The Governor restores order in Woodbury and makes plans to punish those responsible.
name: Home

description: Their security threatened, Rick and the group must make a choice. With Woodbury in a police state, Andrea grows uneasy.
name: I Ain’t A Judas

description: Realizing they are heavily outgunned against the Governor's forces, Rick leads an expedition to get more weapons.
name: Clear

deck: The first episode of the series that chronicles rising conflict of the Clone Wars.
name: Chapter 1

description: In an effort to prevent any more deaths, Rick and the Governor meet to come up with a peace treaty.
name: Arrow On the Doorpost

description: The Governor chases a dissenter who fled Woodbury. While the Governor is gone, a traitor tries to sabotage his upcoming plans.
name: Prey

description: Rick and the group are faced with a serious problem. If they want a truce with the Governor, they will have to make a huge sacrifice.
name: This Sorrowful Life

description: Rick and the group have to seriously consider if the prison is worth defending as the Governor's impending attack looms over their heads.
name: Welcome To the Tombs

deck: A female super soldier approaches Doggett with crucial information.
name: Nothing Important Happened Today

deck: His team become concerned as Doggett is more and more determined to find the truth.
name: Nothing Important Happened Today II

deck: A man seems to have an evil influence over the other patients at the psychiatric ward where he is being treated.
name: Daemonicus

deck: Doggett is attacked by a man who can shift between dimensions.
name: 4-D

deck: A boy has the power to control insects.
name: Lord of the Flies

deck: Mulder and Scully become suspicious of an NSA agent who seems a little too interested in them.
name: Trust No 1

description: Forensic analyst Dexter Morgan hides his double life as a vigilante serial killer from his vice squad officer sister, his coworkers at the Miami Metro Police Department, and his commitment-minded single-mom girlfriend.
name: Dexter

deck: Doggett wakes up in Mexico with severe amnesia, and no recollection of his real identity.
name: John Doe

deck: Reyes investigates a series of deaths in which the victims are completely skinned.
name: Hellbound

deck: An unusual death seems to be connected to the African artifact.
name: Provenance

deck: J'onn Jonzz, the Martian Manhunter, comes to Earth to warn of an impending alien invasion. Part 1 of 3
description: As alien invaders based loosely on the White Martians, who were accidentally awakened on Mars begin to take over the Earth, Superman and Batman rescue J'onn J'onzz who telepathically summons Wonder Woman, Hawkgirl the Flash and Green Lantern to defeat the invasion. Superman gathers everyone at the newly built Watchtower funded by Batman (through Wayne Aerospace's R&D budget) and asks to be part of a team, which he dubs the Justice League.
name: Secret Origins: Part 1

description: Dexter's world is rocked when a rival serial murderer, dubbed the Ice Truck Killer by the media, privately contacts him and reveals that he knows Dexter's grisly secret. Meanwhile, Dexter's sister Debra is transferred to Homicide.
name: Crocodile

deck: A cult become obsessed with Scully's baby.
name: Providence

description: Dexter and Debra try to dissuade their boss from pursuing a security guard they believe he has wrongly identified as the Ice Truck Killer; Dexter's girlfriend receives an unwelcome visit from an associate of her imprisoned husband.
name: Popping Cherry

deck: When Reyes is hospitalised after a serious accident, her life hangs in the balance.
name: Audrey Pauley

deck: Doggett refuses to believe a man is innocent, even after DNA evidence leads to his name being cleared.
name: Underneath

description: The Ice Truck Killer begins leaving body parts from his victims at sites that relate to memories from Dexter's childhood, forcing him to confront his dark personal history.
name: Let's Give the Boy a Hand

description: J'onn Jonzz, the Martian Manhunter, comes to Earth to warn of an impending alien invasion. Part 2 of 3
name: Secret Origins: Part 2

deck: Scully is skeptical when Reyes insists that a killer is using numerological patterns as part of his MO.
name: Improbable

deck: Doggett enlists the help of a rookie in agent while investigating the suspicious relationship between a boy and his father.
name: Scary Monsters

description: The Homicide Division is buzzing after the Ice Truck Killer's latest victim is found mutilated but alive, while Dexter gets in over his head when he stalks a murderous human trafficker.
name: Love, American Style

deck: The Lone Gunmen risk everything to protect the local population from a killer virus.
name: Jump the Shark
